commit.message:
Make sure we read all data in _read_frame() and _recv_sasl_message() (#23)

self._trans.read() usually makes no attempt to read all data, so use
readAll() instead. However, keep the compatibility layer with thriftpy,
as readAll does not exist there, only read, which functions the same
as readAll.

Fixes #22

commit.message:
Use six.ensure_binary to convert strs into bytes in _send_message(). (#19)

Pull request #17 addressed the issue whereby there were occasional
concatenation problems when message header and mesage body were of
different types. However, the original patch, which uses encode(),
was not compatible with python 2 in cases where the body included
characters that fell outside of the strict set of ASCII characters.

commit.message: Modify _send_message to turn body into bytes for proper concatenation with header. (#17)
Change setup.py version to 0.4.0, and pin thrift 0.9.3 for python 2
Fix compatibility with isOpen (Apache Thrift) and is_open (pythrift) (#13)
Fix erorrs in apache thrift compatibility (#10)
Update to use Apache Thrift everywhere, instead of using thriftpy on Python 3. (#6)
Attempt to make the setup.py more cross platform. (#5)
RLS: Bump version to 0.2.1 and add maintainer

Support transports with camelCase method names (#3)

Thrift works with Python 3, but has not renamed the `isOpen` method.
Maybe it will in future, so I've kept the check defensive, and
optimistically choose the pythonic version.
